	In problems 6#, find the boundary of the given set and state whether it is closed, bounded, and/or compact.

	#. $A = \left\{ (x, y) \mid #R#^2 \mid x \leq y \right\}$.

	#. $B = \left\{ (x, y, z) \mid #R#^3 \mid x^2 + y^2 < 1 - z^2 \right\}$.

	#. $C = \left\{ (x, y) \mid #R#^2 \mid y = \sin(x) \text{ and } x \in [0, \pi] \right\}$.

	#. $D = \left\{ (x, y) \mid #R#^2 \mid y = \sin\left( \frac{1}{x} \right) \text{ and } x \in [-\pi, \pi] \right\}$.

	#. $E = \left\{ x \in #R# \mid x \text{ is an integer} \right\}$.

	#. $F = \left\{ x \in #R# \mid x \text{ is a rational number} \right\}$.

