	In problems 3#, give an example of a set $A$ in $#R#^2$ with the following properties or briefly explain why it is impossible.

	#. $A$ is compact and contains infinitely many points.

	#. $A$ is not compact and contains finitely many points.

	#. (Bonus --- challenging) $A$ is not closed but is equal to the boundary of another set $B$.

